entry.summary: ...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 AM MST FRIDAY... * WHAT...Wet snow expected. Additional snow accumulations of up to two to five inches, mainly above 9000 feet in elevation. Winds gusting as high as 40 mph will create reduced visibility at times.

entry.summary: ...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 AM MST FRIDAY... * WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of up to two to four inches. Winds gusting as high as 50 mph. * WHERE...Snowy Range above 9000 feet in elevation. * WHEN...Until 2 AM MST Friday.

entry.title: High Wind Warning issued November 16 at 11:06AM MST until November 17 at 8:00AM MST by NWS
